{"first_name":"Grant","last_name":"Allen","permalink":"grant-allen","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/grant-allen","homepage_url":"","birthplace":"","twitter_username":"grantallen","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"ABB Technology Ventures","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"abb, cleantech, vc, venture, early-stage, growth, storage, solar, core, microsoft, wharton, duke","alias_list":"","created_at":"Tue Nov 18 21:39:26 UTC 2008","updated_at":"Thu Aug 23 16:53:02 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Grant Allen is Vice President of ABB Technology Ventures (ATV), the venture capital arm of ABB, Inc. (NYSE: ABB), the $45 billion global leader in power and automation technology.  ATV is focused on bringing together new technologies, new markets and new talent to discover tomorrow&#8217;s energy solutions and grow ABB&#8217;s global businesses, with a particular focus on smart grid, data centers, energy efficiency, analytics and distribution. </p>\n\n<p>Previously, Mr. Allen was a Vice President with Core Capital Partners, a Washington, D.C.-based venture capital firm with $350 million under management.  Prior to Core Capital, he was a Product Manager at Microsoft Corporation in the Mobile &amp; Embedded Devices division.  </p>\n\n<p>He is also Principal of Keybridge Venture Partners, a Washington D.C. seed fund, and Chairman of the Ocular Melanoma Foundation, a novel non-profit cancer research and advocacy group he founded in 2003.  </p>\n\n<p>Mr. Allen holds a BSE in civil and environmental engineering with honors from Duke University and an MBA from The Wharton School.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,77],"assets/images/resized/0004/8873/48873v1-max-150x150.jpg"],[[250,128],"assets/images/resized/0004/8873/48873v1-max-250x250.jpg"],[[272,140],"assets/images/resized/0004/8873/48873v1-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":""},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"MBA","subject":"","institution":"University of Pennsylvania","grad